dataAnalysis

Class MapData

  • java.lang.Object
    • dataAnalysis.MapData

  • public class MapData
extends java.lang.Object
    This class takes in a weather data file. It sorts the air temperature data (1.5m and 9.0m above the ground) and solar radiation data into distinct observations. Additionally, it calculates helpful statistics including maximum, minimum, and average values for each data type. The class will print these values.
    Version:
    2018-09-25
    Author:
    Robert Hill

      • parseFile

        public void parseFile()
               throws java.io.IOException
        Retrieves the directory and uses the fileName to open a data file. Then, it parses the data file into 3 ArrayLists of observations based off data type. It also calls the parseParamHeader method to find the locations of the desired data types.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
